There were a few challenges I have encountered throughout this therapy clinic network project. For example, I used the wrong cable types and once I replaced it with copper straight through cables there was connectivity. Another challenge I have encountered is the PC could not determine the hostname, so I went into the server and made sure the correct IP address was in the DNS.

The therapy clinic network was designed, connected, and working. All of the devices has their IP address, DNS, ARP, and ICMP working well and correctly. The staff computer is able to communicate with all the other devices, as well as the DNS. Overall, this project has helped me understand how network design and configuration is able to be successfully running.
